<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The parameter 'line' is declared as 'char *' but is only read (not modified); the expression &line[prefix_len] therefore yields a non-const pointer whereas Rule 8.13 requires pointers to point to const-qualified types when possible. In this code 'line' should be declared 'const char *line' and the call become strdup(&line[prefix_len]).
